                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23663: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Vera Cruz</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foster</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="6" xml:id="d142fn6">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, at 5 p.m., to the consul at Frontera.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-23T12:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1920—noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 20, 9 p.m.</p>
                <p>Navy Department is being asked whether it has available war vessel that could be
                    dispatched on reasonably short notice to Ports of Vera Cruz, Puerto México and
                    Frontera should emergency arise appearing to make such action advisable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
